# Thingsly IoT Platform Structure

## Core Directories
- `cmd/`: Command-line tools and utilities
- `configs/`: Configuration files
- `docs/`: Project documentation
- `files/`: File storage
- `initialize/`: System initialization code
- `internal/`: Main project implementation
  - `api/`: API interfaces
  - `app/`: Core application logic
  - `dal/`: Data Access Layer
  - `logic/`: Business logic
  - `middleware/`: HTTP middleware
  - `model/`: Data models
  - `query/`: Query implementations
  - `service/`: Service layer
- `mqtt/`: MQTT protocol implementation
- `pkg/`: External packages
  - `utils/`: Utility functions
  - `errcode/`: Error codes
  - `global/`: Global variables
  - `constant/`: Constants
  - `common/`: Common functions
- `router/`: Route definitions
- `sql/`: Database scripts
- `static/`: Static resources
- `third_party/`: Third-party libraries
- `test/`: Test code

## Technology Stack
- Backend: Go (Gin + Gorm)
- Database: PostgreSQL with TimescaleDB
- Cache: Redis
- Message Queue: MQTT (GMQTT/VerneMQ)
- Access Control: Casbin
- Documentation: Swagger
